The pennsylvania case I cited in  a previous post resulted in a conviction.<br>
<br>
In 1996 (possibly 97, I don't keep track of these things) there was a conviction in Ohio (a U.S. Airman I believe).<br>
<br>
And the 3rd I remember was in Ohio as well.<br>
<br>
I would assume there is quite possibly more fetal homicide convictions  that I don't remember or heard of.<br>
<br>
This case is just getting more publicity and folks are hearing about laws they did not know existed.<br>
